        <Parent_String>building plans [300034157], plans (orthographic projections) [300034104], orthographic projections (images) [300034017], images by method of projection [300068504], images by method of representation [300033974], visual works by form of image [300191088], visual works by form [300191087], visual works (works) [300191086], Visual Works (hierarchy name) [300179869], Visual and Verbal Communication (hierarchy name) [300264552], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Plans that illustrate the configuration and location of the foundation, which comprises the supporting elements of a building, located primarily below ground level, that transmit building loads to the soil or rock underneath. They may also note the conditions that are required for the support of a specific structure.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000042181/Wakita and Linde, Professional Practice (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere a planos que ilustran la configuración y localización de la fundación, que comprende los elementos de soporte de un edificio, localizado principalmente bajo el nivel del suelo, que transmite la carga del edificio al suelo o roca que se encuentra por debajo. También pueden hacer notar las condiciones requeridas para el soporte de una estructura específica.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar plattegronden met de configuratie en ligging van de fundering, oftewel het geheel van dragende elementen van een gebouw, dat zich hoofdzakelijk ondergronds bevindt en de druk van het bouwwerk afvoert naar de grond of het gesteente eronder. Ook kunnen er specifieke eisen met betrekking tot de dragende structuur in zijn opgenomen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000119831/IATE: European Union Terminology (2022-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>呈現地基結構及位置的平面圖，包括建築位於地面下的支撐元素，用於將建築荷重傳導至地下的土壤或岩石。這類圖則有時也用以說明支撐特定結構的必須條件。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Plan, der Lage und Beschaffenheit eines Fundaments sowie die tragenden Elemente eines Gebäudes, die vor allem unterirdisch angelegt sind und die Gebäudelast auf die Erde oder den Felsen darunter ableiten, darstellt. Kann auch Hinweise auf notwendige Bedingungen für die Abstützung einer bestimmten Struktur enthalten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Plantas que ilustram a configuração e localização da fundação, composta pelos elementos que suportam um edifício e que estão localizados abaixo do nível do solo de modo a transmitir as cargas da construção para o solo. Elas também podem conter notas sobre as condições que são necessárias para o suporte de uma estrutura específica.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000179/VP-intern</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000110648/Portuguese Translation Intern Project (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
